documentation.text: @dev Function to migrate V1 CHES tokens to V2 CHES.
@dev Only owner function to withdraw the V1 CHES tokens after users have sent them in the claim their V2 tokens.

@dev Only owner function to withdraw V2 CHES tokens if absolutely necessary.
 @param amount the amount of V2 CHES tokens to withdraw from the token claim contract

natspec.details: Contract for users to claim their v2 tokens 1 for 1 based on their v1 balance at the time of migration.

claimV2CHESTokens().details: Function to migrate V1 CHES tokens to V2 CHES.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setupTokenBalances(address[],uint256[]).details: Only owner function to set the V1 CHES balance of each investor for the V2 CHES token claims.

params.accounts: the list of addresses that held the V1 CHES token.
params.tokenAmount: list of token amounts for each of the V1 CHES holders.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdrawV1CHESTokens().details: Only owner function to withdraw the V1 CHES tokens after users have sent them in the claim their V2 tokens.

withdrawV2CHESTokens(uint256).details: Only owner function to withdraw V2 CHES tokens if absolutely necessary.

params.amount: the amount of V2 CHES tokens to withdraw from the token claim contract
